        <!--
            Project require something that can read JSON and produce a Map<String, Object>
            back! This allows for wrapping this Map with Modelish models that only use
            interfaces and store data in just such a Map structure. A Modelish model
            can take this Map and wrap it with an appropriate model interface. Modelish
            models can be made immutable and can also be cloned which will create a
            complete copy having no references to original source.

            I have never used gson before, but I have now tested it, and it produces exactly
            what is needed here!

            This is what is needed to parse JSON (If I forget what I googled on to find this):

                Gson gson = new Gson();
                Type type = new TypeToken<Map<String, Object>>(){}.getType();
                Map<String, Object> map = gson.fromJson(jsonString, type);

                NOTE TO SELF: Above reads from a String, I need to read from an InputStream!
        -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.google.code.gson</groupId>
            <artifactId>gson</artifactId>
            <version>2.10.1</version>
        </dependency>


